As displayed in Fig. S9 and Fig. S10 (Supporting information), we observed that the papain@AuNCs quenching responded selectively toward Cu2+ over other common metal ions and amino acids. Furthermore, the fluorescence restoring of papain@AuNCs-Cu2+ complex after addition of metal cations (Na+, K+, Li+, Ca2+, Mg2+, Mn2+, Cu2+, Ag+, Hg2+ and Fe3+), anions (HSO3
                        − and S2−), reactive oxygen species (H2O2 and ClO−), reactive nitrogen species (HOONO), glucose, lactic acid, ascorbic acid, uric acid, GSH and amino acids (Phe, Glu, Cys, Val, Met, Tyr, Arg, Trp, Ser and Thr) (Fig. 2
                        ) were investigated to examine the selectivity for sensing D-pen.
